"icon-item__label\">Persistent memory</span>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n\n      <div class=\"callout callout--info\">\n        <span class=\"callout__icon\">💡</span>\n        <div class=\"callout__content\">\n          <div class=\"callout__title\">Why does this matter?</div>\n          Unlike a chatbot in a browser, this AI has access to your actual project files. It can understand the code you're working on, make changes directly, and run tests — not just suggest what to write.\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <!-- Screen 2: The user journey -->\n    <div class=\"screen animate-in\">\n      <h2 class=\"screen__title\">The journey of a single message</h2>\n      <p class=\"text-lead mb-6\">Every time you type a message and press Enter, a carefully choreographed sequence fires up. Here's the ballet behind the scenes.</p>\n\n      <div class=\"step-cards\">\n        <div class=\"step-card\">\n          <div class=\"step-card__num\">1</div>\n          <div>\n            <div class=\"step-card__title\">You type a message</div>\n            <div class=\"step-card__desc\">Something like \"add a login button to the settings page.\" The CLI captures your keystrokes in a text input widget.</div>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"step-card\">\n          <div class=\"step-card__num\">2</div>\n          <div>\n            <div class=\"step-card__title\">The message enters a queue</div>\n            <div class=\"step-card__desc\">If the AI is already busy, your message waits. The queue makes sure the AI doesn't get overwhelmed by a flood of rapid requests.</div>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"step-card\">\n          <div class=\"step-card__num\">3</div>\n          <div>\n            <div class=\"step-card__title\">The AI reads the message and thinks</div>\n            <div class=\"step-card__desc\">The AI model (running on a server somewhere, not your machine) reads your message along with your entire conversation history and project context.</div>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"step-card\">\n          <div class=\"step-card__num\">4</div>\n          <div>\n            <div class=\"step-card__title\">The AI decides to use tools</div>\n            <div class=\"step-card__desc\">It might call a <span class=\"term\" data-tip=\"A function the AI can invoke — like a web search, file read, or shell command. The AI chooses which tools to call based on what you asked.\">tool</span> like \"read this file\" or \"run this command.\" Each tool call pauses the AI's response until the tool returns a result.</div>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"step-card\">\n          <div class=\"step-card__num\">5</div>\n          <div>\n            <div class=\"step-card__title\">Results stream back to you</div>\n            <div class=\"step-card__desc\">The AI's response — and any tool results — appear on screen in real time, character by character, like someone is typing.</div>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <!-- Screen 3: Data flow animation -->\n    <div class=\"screen animate-in\">\n      <h2 class=\"screen__title\">A conversation in motion</h2>\n      <p class=\"text-lead mb-6\">Here's that dance visualized as actors passing messages between each other.</p>\n\n      <div class=\"group-chat\">\n        <div class=\"group-chat__header\">\n          <span>💬</span>\n          <span>Live conversation trace — what happens when you type \"fix the login bug\"</span>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"group-chat__body\">\n          <div class=\"chat-bubble chat-bubble--left\">\n            <div class=\"chat-bubble__sender\">You</div>\n            fix the login bug\n          </div>\n          <div class=\"chat-bubble chat-bubble--center\">\n            Message queued. Waiting for AI...\n          </div>\n          <div class=\"chat-bubble chat-bubble--left\">\n            <div class=\"chat-bubble__sender\">Agent</div>\n            I'll look at the login code. Let me first find the relevant files.\n          </div>\n          <div class=\"chat-bubble chat-bubble--left\">\n            <div class=\"chat-bubble__sender\">Agent</div>\n            <span class=\"typing-indicator\"><span></span><span></span><span></span></span>\n            Reading files...\n          </div>\n          <div class=\"chat-bubble chat-bubble--right\">\n            <div class=\"chat-bubble__sender\">Tool: read_file</div>\n            auth.py — 47 lines read ✓\n          </div>\n          <div class=\"chat-bubble chat-bubble--left\">\n            <div class=\"chat-bubble__sender\">Agent</div>\n            Found it. The session token isn't being refreshed on line 34. Let me fix that.\n          </div>\n          <div class=\"chat-bubble chat-bubble--right\">\n            <div class=\"chat-bubble__sender\">Tool: write_file</div>\n            auth.py — updated ✓\n          </div>\n          <div class=\"chat-bubble chat-bubble--left\">\n            <div class=\"chat-bubble__sender\">Agent</div>\n            Fixed! The token refresh was missing. I've also added a check for token expiry.\n          </div>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <!-- Screen 4: Code translation -->\n    <div class=\"screen animate-in\">\n      <h2 class=\"screen__title\">What the entry point looks like</h2>\n      <p class=\"text-lead mb-6\">When you run <code style=\"background:var(--color-bg-warm);padding:2px 6px;border-radius:4px;font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:0.9em\">deepagents</code>, this is the first code that runs. The CLI decides whether to show the interactive app or handle a one-off command like <code style=\"background:var(--color-bg-warm);padding:2px 6px;border-radius:4px;font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:0.9em\">list</code> or <code style=\"background:var(--color-bg-warm);padding:2px 6px;border-radius:4px;font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:0.9em\">reset</code>.</p>\n\n      <div class=\"translation-block\">\n        <div class=\"translation-block__header\">deepagents_cli/main.py — simplified</div>\n        <div class=\"translation-block__grid\">\n          <div class=\"translation-block__code\">\n<pre class=\"code-pre\"><div class=\"code-line\"><span class=\"code-line__num\">1</span><span>def main() -> int:</div>\n<div class=\"code-line\"><span class=\"code-line__num\">2</span><span>    args = parse_args()</div>\n<div class=\"code-line\"><span class=\"code-line__num\">3</span><span>    if args.command == \"run\":</div>\n<div class=\"code-line\"><span class=\"code-line__num\">4</span><span>        run_app(args)        # ← starts the TUI</div>\n<div class=\"code-line\"><span class=\"code-line__num\">5</span><span>    elif args.command == \"list\":</div>\n<div class=\"code-line\"><span class=\"code-line__num\">6</span><span>        list_agents(args)    # ← prints agent list</div>\n<div class=\"code-line\"><span class=\"code-line__num\">7</span><span>    elif args.command == \"reset\":</div>\n<div class=\"code-line\"><span class=\"code-line__num\">8</span><span>        reset_agent(args)    # ← resets prompt</div>\n<div class=\"code-line\"><span class=\"code-line__num\">9</span><span>    return 0</div></pre>\n          </div>\n          <div class=\"translation-block__english\">\n            <div class=\"english-line\"><strong>Line 1</strong> — Defines the main function. Everything starts here.</div>\n            <div class=\"english-line\"><strong>Line 2</strong> — Reads your command-line arguments (flags like <code style=\"background:rgba(255,255,255,0.1);padding:1px 4px;border-radius:3px\">--agent</code>, <code style=\"background:rgba(255,255,255,0.1);padding:1px 4px;border-radius:3px\">-r</code>).</div>\n            <div class=\"english-line\"><strong>Line 3–4</strong> — If you typed just <code style=\"background:rgba(255,255,255,0.1);padding:1px 4px;border-radius:3px\">deepagents</code> (no subcommand), fire up the interactive app.</div>\n            <div class=\"english-line\"><strong>Line 5–6</strong> — If you typed <code style=\"background:rgba(255,255,255,0.1);padding:1px 4px;border-radius:3px\">deepagents list</code>, print all known agents.</div>\n            <div class=\"english-line\"><strong>Line 7–8</strong> — If you typed <code style=\"background:rgba(255,255,255,0.1);padding:1px 4px;border-radius:3px\">deepagents reset</code>, reset the agent's prompt file.</div>\n            <div class=\"english-line\"><strong>Line 9</strong> — Return 0 means \"success.\" Any other number means an error happened.</div>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <!-- Screen 5: Quiz -->\n    <div class=\"screen animate-in\">\n      <h2 class=\"screen__title\">Check your understanding</h2>\n\n      <div class=\"quiz\" id=\"quiz-module-1\">\n        <div class=\"quiz__question\">You run <code>deepagents list</code>. Which path does the message take?</div>\n        <div class=\"quiz__options\">\n          <button class=\"quiz__option\" data-answer=\"a\">The message goes to the AI model and back</button>\n          <button class=\"quiz__option\" data-answer=\"b\" data-correct=\"true\">A separate code path handles it — no AI involved, just file listing</button>\n          <button class=\"quiz__option\" data-answer=\"c\">It queues behind any existing agent conversation</button>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"quiz__feedback quiz__feedback--correct\" data-for=\"b\">Exactly! <code>deepagents list</code> is a <span class=\"term\" data-tip=\"A subcommand — a second-level command that does something specific, separate from the main app.\">subcommand</span> that bypasses the AI entirely. It just reads the ~/.deepagents directory and prints what it finds. Same with <code>deepagents reset</code> and <code>deepagents skills</code>.</div>\n        <div class=\"quiz__feedback quiz__feedback--incorrect\" data-for=\"a\">Not quite — subcommands like <code>list</code> don't go near the AI at all. They're handled by separate functions that just read directories and print results.</div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n  </div>\n</section>\n\nHTMLEOF\necho \"Module 1 done\"",
