el Selection\n\nUsers can select models via:\n- Config: `[models] default = \"opencode:gpt-5.1-codex\"`\n- CLI: `--model opencode:kimi-k2.5`\n- Runtime: `/model opencode:kimi-k2.5`\n\n### Implementation Requirements\n\n1. Add `\"opencode\": \"OPENCODE_API_KEY\"` to `PROVIDER_API_KEY_ENV` in `model_config.py`\n2. Update test assertions in `test_model_config.py`\n3. Document usage in CLI help\n\n### Model Lists\n\nInitial OpenAI-compatible models:\n- **Zen**: `gpt-5.1-codex`, `gpt-5.2`\n- **Go**: `glm-5`, `kimi-k2.5`\n\n(MiniMax models require Anthropic-compatible endpoint — deferred for now)",
            "oldString": "# OpenCode Provider Support Design\n\n## Overview\n\nAdd support for OpenCode's Zen and Go services as model providers in the CLI through user configuration.\n\n## Background\n\nOpenCode offers two paid services:\n- **Zen**: Pay-as-you-go ($20 minimum) at `opencode.ai/zen/v1/chat/completions` — OpenAI-compatible API\n- **Go**: Subscription ($5 first month, $10/mo) with two endpoints:\n  - OpenAI-compatible: `opencode.ai/zen/go/v1/chat/completions` — GLM-5, Kimi K2.5\n  - Anthropic-compatible: `opencode.ai/zen/go/v1/messages` — MiniMax M2.5, M2.7\n\nUsers can access these models via API keys through the `/connect` command in OpenCode, or by obtaining API keys from opencode.ai/auth.\n\n## Design\n\n### Configuration\n\nUsers configure two providers in `~/.deepagents/config.toml`:\n\n```toml\n[models.providers.opencode-zen]\napi_key_env = \"OPENCODE_ZEN_API_KEY\"\nbase_url = \"https://opencode.ai/zen/v1\"\nmodels = [\n    \"gpt-5.1-codex\",\n    \"gpt-5.2\",\n    # Add models as OpenCode adds them\n]\n\n[models.providers.opencode-go]\napi_key_env = \"OPENCODE_GO_API_KEY\"\nbase_url = \"https://opencode.ai/zen/go/v1\"\nmodels = [\n    \"glm-5\",\n    \"kimi-k2.5\",\n    \"minimax-m2.5\",\n    \"minimax-m2.7\",\n]\n```\n\n### Environment Variables\n\nUsers set:\n```bash\nexport OPENCODE_ZEN_API_KEY=\"sk-...\"\nexport OPENCODE_GO_API_KEY=\"sk-...\"\n```\n\n### Model Selection\n\nUsers can select models via:\n- Config: `[models] default = \"opencode-zen:gpt-5.1-codex\"`\n- CLI: `--model opencode-go:kimi-k2.5`\n- Runtime: `/model opencode-go:kimi-k2.5`\n\n### Implementation Requirements\n\n1. Add `\"opencode-zen\"` and `\"opencode-go\"` to `PROVIDER_API_KEY_ENV` in `model_config.py`\n2. Update test assertions in `test_model_config.py`\n3. Document usage in CLI help (via AGENTS.md or separate docs)\n\n### Model Lists\n\nInitial model lists:\n- **opencode-zen**: `gpt-5.1-codex`, `gpt-5.2`\n- **opencode-go**: `glm-5`, `kimi-k2.5`, `minimax-m2.5`, `minimax-m2.7`\n\nUsers should verify current models at opencode.ai/docs/zen and opencode.ai/go.\n\n## Trade-offs\n\n- Simple config-only approach — no custom class_path needed\n- Uses existing LangChain OpenAI provider (for OpenAI-compatible endpoints)\n- Requires users to manually update model lists as OpenCode adds new models\n- Single base_url per provider — handles both Zen and Go as separate providers\n\n## Edge Cases\n\n- API key not set: Shows warning icon in model switcher (via `has_provider_credentials`)\n- Invalid API key: Handled by LangChain provider at call time\n- Rate limits: Handled by LangChain/OpenCode API\n\n## Testing\n\n- Unit tests for credential detection\n- Integration tests for model creation (if possible without real API keys)"
