            "newString": "# OpenCode Provider Support Design\n\n## Overview\n\nAdd support for OpenCode's Zen and Go services as model providers in the CLI through user configuration.\n\n## Background\n\nOpenCode uses a **single API key** for both Zen and Go services. Users obtain the key from opencode.ai/auth.\n\n### API Endpoints (from docs)\n\n**Zen** (`https://opencode.ai/zen/v1`):\n| Models | Endpoint | Compatible with |\n|--------|----------|-----------------|\n| GPT-5.x | `/responses` | OpenAI |\n| Claude | `/messages` | Anthropic |\n| Gemini | `/models/{model}` | Google |\n| MiniMax, GLM, Kimi | `/chat/completions` | OpenAI-compatible |\n\n**Go** (`https://opencode.ai/zen/go/v1`):\n| Models | Endpoint | Compatible with |\n|--------|----------|-----------------|\n| GLM-5, Kimi K2.5 | `/chat/completions` | OpenAI-compatible |\n| MiniMax M2.5, M2.7 | `/messages` | Anthropic |\n\n### Limitation\n\nLangChain's OpenAI provider defaults to `/v1/chat/completions`. Models using `/responses` (GPT) or `/messages` (Claude, MiniMax-Go) require different endpoint paths.\n\n**This design supports only the models that work with `/chat/completions`.**\n\n## Design\n\n### Two Providers\n\nUsers configure both Zen and Go in `~/.deepagents/config.toml`:\n\n```toml\n[models.providers.opencode-zen]\napi_key_env = \"OPENCODE_API_KEY\"\nbase_url = \"https://opencode.ai/zen/v1\"\nmodels = [\n    # OpenAI-compatible (via /chat/completions)\n    \"gpt-5.1-codex\",\n    \"gpt-5.2\",\n    \"gpt-5.3-codex\",\n    \"gpt-5.3-codex-spark\",\n    \"gpt-5.4\",\n    \"gpt-5.4-mini\",\n    \"gpt-5.4-nano\",\n    \"glm-5\",\n    \"kimi-k2.5\",\n    \"minimax-m2.5\",\n    \"minimax-m2.5-free\",\n    \"big-pickle\",\n    \"mimo-v2-pro-free\",\n    \"mimo-v2-omni-free\",\n    \"nemotron-3-super-free\",\n]\n\n[models.providers.opencode-go]\napi_key_env = \"OPENCODE_API_KEY\"\nbase_url = \"https://opencode.ai/zen/go/v1\"\nmodels = [\n    # OpenAI-compatible (via /chat/completions)\n    \"glm-5\",\n    \"kimi-k2.5\",\n]\n```\n\n### Environment Variables\n\n```bash\nexport OPENCODE_API_KEY=\"sk-...\"  # Works for both Zen and Go\n```\n\n### Model Selection\n\nUsers select via:\n- Config: `[models] default = \"opencode-zen:kimi-k2.5\"` or `[models] default = \"opencode-go:kimi-k2.5\"`\n- CLI: `--model opencode-zen:glm-5` or `--model opencode-go:kimi-k2.5`\n\n### Implementation Requirements\n\n1. Add `\"opencode-zen\": \"OPENCODE_API_KEY\"` to `PROVIDER_API_KEY_ENV` in `model_config.py`\n2. Add `\"opencode-go\": \"OPENCODE_API_KEY\"` to `PROVIDER_API_KEY_ENV` in `model_config.py`\n3. Add test assertions in `test_model_config.py`\n\n### Supported Models\n\n**opencode-zen** (base_url: `https://opencode.ai/zen/v1`):\n- gpt-5.1-codex, gpt-5.2, gpt-5.3-codex, gpt-5.3-codex-spark, gpt-5.4, gpt-5.4-mini, gpt-5.4-nano\n- glm-5, kimi-k2.5, minimax-m2.5, minimax-m2.5-free\n- big-pickle, mimo-v2-pro-free, mimo-v2-omni-free, nemotron-3-super-free\n\n**opencode-go** (base_url: `https://opencode.ai/zen/go/v1`):\n- glm-5, kimi-k2.5\n\n### Unsupported (require different endpoint or provider)\n\n- Claude models (use `/messages` endpoint)\n- Gemini models (use `/models/{model}` endpoint)\n- Go MiniMax models (use `/messages` endpoint)\n\nFuture enhancement could add support for these endpoints.",
